  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>NHS Business Definition: Orthotist - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
  <div>
      <p>
An 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_orthotist">Orthotist</xref>
 is a 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_care_professional">CARE PROFESSIONAL</xref>
 who is registered with the 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_health_and_care_professions_council">Health and Care Professions Council</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
An 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_orthotist">Orthotist</xref>
 is responsible for all aspects of supplying orthoses for 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENTS</xref>.        </p>
      <p>An orthosis is a device fitted to an existing body part in order to improve its function or reduce pain.</p>
      <p>
         <i>
Note: also see 
                  <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                  keyref="business_definition_prosthetist">Prosthetist</xref>.            </i>
      </p>
  </div>
